      Reference Document     http://www.w3.org/WAI/UA/WAI-USERAGENT-19990709/    Hello,    In looking at the section on conformance [1] in the 9 July  draft, I see the following sentences:    > In order to conform as a desktop graphical user agent,   > the user agent must do all of the following:    >   1.Satisfy all the Priority 1 checkpoints listed  >     in this document that apply to that class of   >     user agent, and     >   2.Satisfy those checkpoints natively unless the   >     checkpoint explicitly indicates that it may be  >     satisfied through communication with other software.     We make use of point 1 by distinguishing desktop graphical  user agents from dependent user agents in some checkpoints.    However, I don't see any checkpoints where we say that  conformance is possible by communication with other software.    I propose that we discuss point 2. at the next teleconference  and consider dropping it. I suspect that it's role has  been subsumed by point 1. in practice.     - Ian    [1] http://www.w3.org/WAI/UA/WAI-USERAGENT-19990709/#conformance      --   Ian Jacobs (jacobs@w3.org)   http://www.w3.org/People/Jacobs  Tel/Fax:                     +1 212 684-1814        

