      Hello,    I discussed the conformance provisions of the guidelines   (Candidate Rec [1]) yesterday with Dan Connolly and have  made one addition and some editorial changes, listed below.    The old version of "Well-formed conformance claims"  required only the version number and operating system,  but not, for example, the name of the product or the vendor.    I propose the following new text:    <BLOCKQUOTE>  A well-formed claim must include the following information:       About the guidelines:        -  The guidelines title/version: "User Agent Accessibility  Guidelines 1.0".        -  The URI of the guidelines:  http://www.w3.org/TR/2000/CR-UAAG10-20000128.        -  The conformance level satisfied: "A", "Double-A", or "Triple-A".        -    The checkpoints of the chosen conformance level considered            not applicable. Claimants should use the checklist  [UAAG10-CHECKLIST] for           this purpose.     About the subject of the claim:        -  <NEW>The vendor name.</NEW>       -  The <NEW>product name</NEW> and version number.        -  The operating system name and version number.     Properties of the claim:        -  The date of the claim.   </BLOCKQUOTE>    Later on in the section "Validity of a claim", I've  made a strong link between the second bullet and the "subject  of the claim" (which is named in the previous section):    <BLOCKQUOTE>     A conformance claim is valid for a given conformance level if:      1.The claim is well-formed, and       2.The subject of the claim satisfies all the applicable         checkpoints for that level.   </BLOCKQUOTE>      Please let me know if there are any objections to these changes.       - Ian    [1] http://www.w3.org/TR/2000/CR-UAAG10-20000128   --   Ian Jacobs (jacobs@w3.org)   http://www.w3.org/People/Jacobs  Tel/Fax:                     +1 212 684-1814 or 212 532-4767  Cell:                        +1 917 450-8783        

