ntionally does not identify the set of  > "important elements" that must be navigable; refer to the Techniques  > document [UAAG10-TECHS] for information about identifying important  > elements. [ETC.] User agents should follow operating system conventions for  > indicating navigation progress (e.g., selection or content focus)."  >   > "Technique for checkpoint 7.8: Allow forward and backward sequential  > navigation to elements with same style as the current element."  >   > "7.9 Allow the user to configure and control the set of important elements  > required by checkpoint 7.8. Allow the user to include and exclude element  > types in the set of elements. [Priority 3]  > Note: For example, allow the user to navigate only [ETC.]  >   > <END OF MEMO>  > =  > ===========================  > Eric G. Hansen, Ph.D.  > Development Scientist  > Educational Testing Service  > ETS 12-R  > Princeton, NJ 08541  > 609-734-5615 (Voice)  > E-mail: ehansen@ets.org  > (W) 609-734-5615 (Voice)  > FAX 609-734-1090    --   Ian Jacobs (jacobs@w3.org)   http://www.w3.org/People/Jacobs  Tel:                         +1 831 457-2842  Cell:                        +1 917 450-8783        

