      Hello,    As per my action item of [1], here's a proposed NEW checkpoint  about form orientation based on Gregory Rosmaita's original proposal  [2].  (It resembles checkpoint 9.6 of [3], for links).    Provide information about the structure and navigation mechanisms  specified for a form. [Priority 2].     For instance, provide information about controls with explicitly     associated labels, about which keys activate the form controls,     about the serial navigation order of the form controls, and     about control groups (e.g., in HTML specified with the FIELDSET     and OPTGROUP elements).     We should also include cross-references about device-independent  activation and navigation.    Since checkpoint 9.10 deals with labels, it could be subsumed  by this proposed checkpoint. Checkpoint 9.10 reads:     Provide the user with access to any label explicitly    associated with a form control. [Priority 2]      - Ian      [1]  http://www.w3.org/WAI/UA/1999/09/wai-ua-telecon-19990915.html#minutes  [2] http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/w3c-wai-ua/1999JulSep/0127.html  [3] http://www.w3.org/WAI/UA/WAI-USERAGENT-19990827   --   Ian Jacobs (jacobs@w3.org)   http://www.w3.org/People/Jacobs  Tel/Fax:                     +1 212 684-1814  Cell:                        +1 917 450-8783        

