      Hello,    In response to the resolution of issue 404 [1] to include a  requirement to allow access to the full range of values if  text decorations are used to distinguish text, I propose the  following definition of "text decoration".       In this document, a "text decoration" means any stylistic      effect that the user agent may apply to visually rendered      text that does not affect the layout of the document      (i.e., does not require reformatting when applied or      removed). Text decoration mechanisms include underline,     overline, and strike-through.     - Ian    [1] http://server.rehab.uiuc.edu/ua-issues/issues-linear-lc2.html#404  --   Ian Jacobs (jacobs@w3.org)   http://www.w3.org/People/Jacobs  Tel:                         +1 831 457-2842  Cell:                        +1 917 450-8783        

